OL,6,FA victim impact statement read in
OL,7,Fcourt by the prosecution during the
OL,8,Fsentencing said Mr Rushworth had had
OL,9,Fto step up his personal safety,
OL,10,Fincluding fitting a panic alarm and
OL,11,Fextra cameras at home.
OL,13,FThe MP said: "He has repeated on
OL,14,Fmultiple occasions his intent to kill
OL,15,Fme and harm my family.
OL,17,F"I do not know whether he is capable
OL,18,Fof carrying out his threats, but it
OL,19,Fhas become increasingly apparent that
OL,20,Fhe is obsessed with me and harbours a
OL,21,Fstrong and irrational hatred.
